{
  "texts": [
    "Vygotsky's concept has profoundly influenced educational research and practice, underpinning contemporary approaches that prioritize PL experiences designed to meet learners at their point of need and help bridge their knowledge gaps (Chaiklin, 2003; Wood et al., 1976).",
    "Previous research on PL suggests that information about a learner, obtained from available data or choices they make, can be utilized to adapt various features of the learning environment (Normadhi et al., 2019; Rane, 2023; Zhang et al., 2020).",
    "This adaptation aims to enhance learning outcomes and create a more effective learning experience for each learner.",
    "We first articulate the basic levels of PL enabled by ChatGPT:",
    "(The 1 st level aligns with the foundational aspect of ZPD, where the learner is seeking assistance to bridge the gap between their current understanding and what they need to learn."
  ]
}